  "title": "Sales Administrative Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong><br /><br />Support the sales team by managing order processing, preparing quotations, issuing work orders, and ensuring timely delivery of goods while providing responsive customer service and after-sales support.</p><p><br /><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Process sales orders accurately using the ERP system </li><li>Prepare quotations, check and enter plan drawings and glass measurements into ERP system to issue work orders and related documents </li><li>Respond promptly to customer inquiries to provide clear and accurate information </li><li>Monitor work progress and coordinate with various departments to ensure timely delivery of goods to customers</li><li>Assist in sales marketing activities by preparing sample kits and supporting sales reviews</li><li>Provide after-sales support by collecting customer feedback and addressing concerns</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 1 year of experience in Sales Administration or Coordinator within the construction industry</li><li>Able to work 5.5 days per week (alternate Saturday)</li><li>Need to liaise with Mandarin speaking customers</li></ul>",
